      },
      "date": "2013-09-05 23:27:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(2 inline comments)\n\nThere appear to be many places where lustre_cfg_new() is called without any error checking at all and then immediately dereferenced.  I don't consider \"LASSERT(lcfg)\" or \"LASSERT(lcfg && !IS_ERR(lcfg))\" to be error handling.\n\nCould you please update this patch to fix all of the callers, and while there change \"if (!lcfg)\" to \"if (lcfg == NULL)\" to match the coding style.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
