          "email": "Isaac_Huang@xyratex.com",
          "date": "2012-05-11 23:42:44.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-1399 config: lustre_cfg_new() should return NULL",
        "message": "LU-1399 config: lustre_cfg_new() should return NULL\n\nAll lustre_cfg_new() callers but one checks its return against\nNULL, but it currently returns ERR_PTR(-ENOMEM). As there's no\nother error to return, lustre_cfg_new() should simply return NULL.\n\nIn ptlrpc_check_status(), the branch to suppress console error on\nPTL_RPC_MSG_ERR replies will never execute, because an identical\ncheck for PTL_RPC_MSG_ERR at the beginning of the function has\nreturned on such cases.\n\nSigned-off-by: Isaac Huang <Isaac_Huang@xyratex.com>\nChange-Id: Id39b0eea100ea952be37eca30e9cdac02b63a1af\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
